  "texts": [
    "However, our SFT mixture deliberately includes short-form, verifiable QA tasks that still require search, so the model learns to handle both concise answers and multi-paragraph long answers.",
    "We therefore examine how well our SFT and RL models perform on standard short-form QA benchmarks to determine how well our approach generalizes to varied query types.",
    "Our short-form evaluation suite comprises SimpleQA (Wei et al., 2024), WebWalkerQA (Wu et al., 2025a), and 2Wiki (Ho et al., 2020).",
    "For short-form QA, we follow prior work (Li et al., 2025a; Wei et al., 2024) and use an LLM judge to determine answer correctness against the annotated gold, reporting 0 200 400 600 1000 1900 RL training steps 10 20 30 40 50 Score (%) Healthbench 0 200 400 600 1000 1900 RL training steps 60 65 70 75 80 85 Score (%) SQAv2 0 200 400 600 1000 1900 RL training steps 15 20 25 30 35 40 Score (%) DRB On Policy SFT Our SFT Undertrained SFT No SFT Figure 7 Performance of different starting point models throughout RL training.",
    "We vary the SFT model used at the start of RL training, and then train using the same data and hyperparameters."
  ]
